        <img src="./media/papunya-from-the-air-data.jpg" alt="image of Papunya" height="300"></img>

        <p>Papunya/Warumpi, NT</p>

        <!-- speaker notes -->
        <aside class="notes">
          So my name is Matt I'm a Luritja/Arrernte and German/Irish mix.
          in my language and culture I have a few names. My formal name
          is Ngamurarri after my famous painter uncle "Mick Ngamurarri"
          of the Papunya Tula arts movement. I have a few other names like
          Tjapaltjarri, Kalibabu etc. But you can just call me Matt.

          My family come from around this small remote community
          in central Australia called Papunya or Warumpi and from communities even further west.
          I spent the first few years of my life here.

          I was first exposed to computers through my dad, who had an old laptop
          that was the size of a small brief case.
